#------------------------------------------------
# spec is the spectrum normalized to unit mean
#------------------------------------------------
def normalizeSpec(spc):
    d = np.sum(spc, axis=1)/len(wave)
    spec = (spc.T/d).T;
    plt.plot(spec.T)
    plt.show()
    return spec

spec = normalizeSpec(spc)

    x2 = Teff[b]
    y2 = logG[b]

In [305]:
def makeGrid(n):
#-------------------------------------------
# create grid of nodes and a list of edges
#-------------------------------------------
    ix = FeH==vF[n]
    nodes = np.where(ix)[0]
    edges = []
    #----------------------------
    # add the horizontal edges
    #----------------------------
    for a in nodes:
        for b in nodes:
            if(logG[a]!=logG[b]):
                continue
            if(Teff[b]-Teff[a] != 1000):
                continue
            edges.append((a,b))
    #        print (a,b, logG[a], logG[b], Teff[a], Teff[b])

    #----------------------------
    # add the vertical edges
    #----------------------------
    for a in nodes:
        for b in nodes:
            if(Teff[a]!=Teff[b]):
                continue
            if(logG[b]-logG[a] != 0.5):
                continue
            edges.append((a,b))
    #        print (a,b, logG[a], logG[b], Teff[a], Teff[b])
    return nodes, edges

In [361]:
def plotPCAGrid(mx,my,cc,cm):
    plt.figure(figsize=(16,5))
    x = v[mx,:]
    y = v[my,:]
    plt.scatter(x[nodes],y[nodes],s=24,c=(cc[nodes]), cmap=cm)
    plt.colorbar()
    plt.xlabel('pca('+str(mx)+')')
    plt.ylabel('pca('+str(my)+')')
    for e in edges:
        plt.plot([x[e[0]], x[e[1]]], [y[e[0]], y[e[1]]],'k-',linewidth=0.3)
    plt.show()
